Structured knowledge bases (KBs) like Wikidata [wikidata], DBpedia [dbpedia], and Yago [yago] are backbones of the semantic web and are employed in many knowledge-centric applications like search, question answering and dialogue. Constructing these KBs at high quality and scale is a long-standing research challenge and multiple knowledge base construction benchmarks exist, e.g., FB15k [bordes2013translating], CoDEx [safavi2020codex], and LM-KBC22 [singhania2022lm]. Text-extraction, knowledge graph embeddings, and LM-based knowledge extraction have continuously moved scores upwards on these tasks, and leaderboard portals like Paperswithcode\footnote{\url{https://paperswithcode.com/task/knowledge-graph-completion}} provide evidence to that.